{"body":"\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai --\u003e\n\u003c!-- walkthrough_start --\u003e\n\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003e📝 Walkthrough\u003c/summary\u003e\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nThis pull request introduces significant documentation expansion (bilingual Spanish/English content, methodology guides, AI development lab framing) alongside a critical startup timing fix and test additions. The core code changes reorder coordinator initialization and EMHASS cache population to ensure proper data readiness during sensor setup. Additionally, a constraint is added to prevent invalid timing calculations when charging windows are too short for computed requirements.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Core Startup Ordering Fix** \u003cbr\u003e `custom_components/ev_trip_planner/__init__.py`|Moves `coordinator.async_config_entry_first_refresh()` before `trip_manager.publish_deferrable_loads()`, ensuring coordinator data is populated before EMHASS cache initialization and guarding the publish call with `if emhass_adapter is not None`.|\n|**EMHASS Adapter Cache Constraint** \u003cbr\u003e `custom_components/ev_trip_planner/emhass_adapter.py`|Adds validation that computed `total_hours` cannot exceed available EMHASS charging window (`def_end_timestep - def_start_timestep`), preventing invalid per-trip cache entries when SOC requirements exceed the planning horizon.|\n|**EMHASS Frontend Parameters** \u003cbr\u003e `custom_components/ev_trip_planner/frontend/panel.js`|Updates Jinja2 template documentation to include three new deferrable-load configuration parameters (`treat_deferrable_load_as_semi_cont`, `set_deferrable_load_single_constant`, `set_deferrable_startup_penalty`) and revises parameter count from 6 to 8.|\n|**Window Mismatch Test Coverage** \u003cbr\u003e `tests/test_def_total_hours_window_mismatch.py`|Adds two new async pytest tests validating that per-trip `def_total_hours` respects the EMHASS charging window bounds when SOC is very low and charging time would otherwise exceed available window duration.|\n|**Bug Investigation Documentation** \u003cbr\u003e `.research/restart_empty_sensor_bug.md`, `research_bug_hypothesis_entry_data_options.md`, `specs/emhass-integration-with-fixes/.progress.md`|Documents investigation into coordinator refresh timing, EMHASS cache population race conditions, and entry.data vs entry.options configuration storage with detailed causal chains and verification recommendations.|\n|**Bilingual Documentation Translation** \u003cbr\u003e `CHANGELOG.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `RELEASE_NOTES_v0.5.*`, `ROADMAP.md`, `TODO.md`, `docs/CODEGUIDELINESia.md`, `docs/MILESTONE_*.md`, `docs/RALPH_METHODOLOGY.md`, `docs/TDD_METHODOLOGY.md`, `docs/TESTING_E2E.md`, `docs/e2e-date-diagnosis-final.md`, `test-analysis.md`|Translates existing Spanish documentation to English with consistent localization across release notes, methodology guides, technical guidelines, and testing documentation; maintains structure and code examples while rewriting all narrative content.|\n|**Spanish Documentation Versions** \u003cbr\u003e `CHANGELOG.es.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.es.md`, `RELEASE_NOTES_v0.5.*.es.md`, `ROADMAP.es.md`, `TODO.es.md`, `docs/CODEGUIDELINESia.es.md`, `docs/MILESTONE_*.es.md`, `docs/RALPH_METHODOLOGY.es.md`, `docs/TDD_METHODOLOGY.es.md`, `docs/TESTING_E2E.es.md`, `docs/e2e-date-diagnosis-final.es.md`, `test-analysis.es.md`|Introduces complete Spanish versions of key documentation files (changelogs, release notes, guidelines, methodology, and testing guides) to support bilingual repository access.|\n|**AI Development Lab \u0026 Portfolio** \u003cbr\u003e `docs/PORTFOLIO.md`, `docs/ai-development-lab.md`, `docs/ai-development-lab.es.md`, `README.md`|Establishes project framing as both a production Home Assistant integration and an AI-assisted development laboratory, includes methodology evolution timeline, architecture flow, phase-by-phase technical debt management, and recruiter-facing metrics; README gains lab attribution block.|\n|**Methodology \u0026 Planning Documentation** \u003cbr\u003e `CLAUDE.es.md`, `doc/gaps/EXECUTIVE_SUMMARY.md`, `doc/gaps/promptspecrfactor.md`, `docs/MILESTONE_4_1_PLANNING.es.md`, `docs/MILESTONE_4_POWER_PROFILE.es.md`, `docs/MILESTONE_4_1_PLANNING.md`, `docs/MILESTONE_4_POWER_PROFILE.md`|Introduces structured development methodology (CLAUDE multi-phase workflow, SOLID refactoring roadmap, gap prioritization summary) alongside detailed milestone specifications for intelligent power profiles and planned v4.1 features (distributed charging, multi-EV support, climate adaptation).|\n|**Strategic Analysis \u0026 Planning** \u003cbr\u003e `plans/john-pm-analysis-ai-dev-lab.md`, `plans/mary-ba-analysis-ai-dev-lab.md`, `plans/winston-architect-review-ai-dev-lab.md`, `plans/unified-change-plan.md`|Adds multi-perspective evaluations (product manager, business analyst, architect reviews) of AI lab messaging, positioning, technical claims, and metrics; consolidates into unified prioritized action plan for recruiter-facing documentation improvements.|\n|**E2E Testing Configuration \u0026 Documentation** \u003cbr\u003e `playwright-env.local.es.md`, `ui-map.local.es.md`, `test-analysis.es.md`, `test-analysis.md`|Establishes E2E environment configuration (browser/auth/locale settings), detailed UI element selector maps for Home Assistant integration flows and panel navigation, and test failure analysis for persistence/cleanup scenarios with expected outcomes and debug guidance.|\n|**Index \u0026 Specification Metadata** \u003cbr\u003e `specs/.index/index-state.json`, `specs/.index/index.md`, `docs/index.md`|Updates spec registry timestamps and phases; refreshes documentation index with new AI Development Lab navigation section, Spanish content links, recruiter/evaluator reading paths, and revised test inventory counts (unit: 70→85, E2E: 7→8).|\n\n## Estimated code review effort\n\n🎯 4 (Complex) | ⏱️ ~60 minutes\n\n## Possibly related PRs\n\n- **#27** — Main PR and PR `#27` both modify EMHASS-related implementation (emhass\\_adapter adjustments and frontend panel.js) to fix deferrable-load and startup/publishing ordering issues.\n- **#32** — Main PR's reordering of coordinator first-refresh before EMHASS publish directly addresses the same async\\_setup\\_entry startup ordering and cache initialization concerns as PR `#32`.\n- **#22** — Main PR's reordering of async\\_setup\\_entry to perform coordinator first-refresh aligns with PR `#22`'s refactoring of TripPlannerCoordinator initialization and entry.runtime\\_data lifecycle changes.\n\n## Poem\n\n\u003e 🐰 *A warren of docs now bilingual and bright,*  \n\u003e *Spanish and English both shining with light,*  \n\u003e *The coordinator dashes ahead with its cache,*  \n\u003e *Before EMHASS can publish or crash,*  \n\u003e *While windows and hours dance into the night!* ✨\n\n\u003c/details\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- walkthrough_end --\u003e\n\n\n\u003c!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start --\u003e\n\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003e🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 5\u003c/summary\u003e\n\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003e✅ Passed checks (5 passed)\u003c/summary\u003e\n\n|         Check name         | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |\n| :------------------------: | :------- | :--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|      Description Check     | ✅ Passed | Check skipped - CodeRabbit’s high-level summary is enabled.                                                                                                                                        